00:15:20,816 --> 00:15:24,938
we've kind of got a captive audience out at GDC when we run the parties because there's

227
00:15:24,978 --> 00:15:28,300
already a really big, enthusiastic indie games audience there.

228
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:32,635
But then coming to the most recent event that we did in London,

229
00:15:32,715 --> 00:15:36,338
which was, as I say, it was on a fucking boat.

230
00:15:36,538 --> 00:15:39,460
And that was the first event in the UK

231
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,061
where we charged entry for.

232
00:15:41,141 --> 00:15:43,743
Because as this audience grows and as we manage

233
00:15:43,783 --> 00:15:45,604
to reach these bigger creative audiences that

234
00:15:45,644 --> 00:15:48,386
sit outside this sort of games literate sort of audience,

235
00:15:48,446 --> 00:15:50,227
that of course, the costs.

236
00:15:50,327 --> 00:15:51,408
And we need a bigger boat.

237
00:15:51,428 --> 00:15:52,349
We need a bigger venue.

238
00:15:52,389 --> 00:15:53,489
We need bigger spaces.

239
00:15:53,529 --> 00:15:55,171
And because of that, that costs money.

240
00:15:55,211 --> 00:15:57,672
And we want to put on these bigger exhibitions and larger

241
00:15:57,772 --> 00:15:58,473
showcases.

242
00:15:59,115 --> 00:16:00,976
But to do that, it costs more money.

243
00:16:01,076 --> 00:16:03,117
And so we had to put a ticket price on the event.

244
00:16:03,217 --> 00:16:05,658
And it was great that our attendance was sort of double

245
00:16:05,698 --> 00:16:06,898
what it was for the first event.

246
00:16:06,958 --> 00:16:09,259
But what we did find retrospectively was sort of

247
00:16:09,319 --> 00:16:11,620
being at that event is that you could see by the audience

248
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:14,821
who had attended that it wasn't quite the same balance

249
00:16:14,861 --> 00:16:16,221
that we'd had for the first event.

