00:16:26,626 --> 00:16:30,727
So I think it's something that retrospectively I want to look back at what ways we can work

255
00:16:30,747 --> 00:16:34,349
to potentially still make sure that we're building these events up and we're able to

256
00:16:34,389 --> 00:16:35,169
grow with the demand.

257
00:16:35,209 --> 00:16:39,972
But also making sure that we remain sort of open, neutral spaces that do welcome people

258
00:16:40,012 --> 00:16:44,574
from outside of this space to come and realize that, okay, so that they don't, you don't

259
00:16:44,614 --> 00:16:48,035
feel that you necessarily like games or you don't classify yourself as a gamer.

260
00:16:48,802 --> 00:16:51,263
But there are things here that you can get passionate about.

261
00:16:51,303 --> 00:16:56,124
And we need to create events and build this sense of culture

262
00:16:56,144 --> 00:16:57,984
and community around these things.

